        The clear, slow-melt, crystalline Gourmet cube is what craft bars specify precisely because cocktail
        programs live or die on dilution control. A cloudy, fast-melting cube from a standard ice machine
        destroys the spirit-to-water ratio a bartender spent months calibrating. The Gourmet cube doesn't.
      </p>
      <p>
        The service implication: when a Brilliance unit goes down in an LA bar, especially on a Thursday-through-Saturday
        night, it's a real revenue emergency. The bar either closes or switches to a lower-tier ice that the
        program was specifically designed against — and customers notice. Our techs understand this timeline.
        After-hours emergency dispatch for craft-cocktail clients is built into our response protocol for WeHo,
        DTLA, Santa Monica, Silver Lake, and Arts District craft-bar clusters.
      </p>
      <p>
        Technical note on Brilliance service: the evaporator architecture is distinct from standard Prodigy Plus
        cube-plate machines. Scale and harvest-dynamic issues look different. Freeze timing, harvest triggering,
        and cube-release mechanics all follow Brilliance-specific patterns. Our service work on these units is
        informed by the specific unit profiles, not generic ice-machine procedures.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="wrap narrow">
      <h2>Meridian MXG nugget — Chick-fil-A, Sonic, and LA fast-casual chain expansion</h2>
      <p>
        Scotsman Meridian MXG is what LA Chick-fil-A franchise kitchens run to produce their signature soft
        chewable nugget ice — the category-defining ice that Chick-fil-A built a cult following around. LA has
        over 25 Chick-fil-A locations as of 2026, plus a growing footprint of Sonic Drive-In locations, Raising
        Cane's stores, and the broader fast-casual segment running nugget ice as a format choice. Meridian
        service is steady work across that base.
      </p>
      <p>
        The Meridian architecture is different from Prodigy Plus cube machines: water forms slush inside a cooled
        cylindrical chamber, an auger rotates to move the slush through a compression chamber, and the
        resulting nugget extrudes into the storage bin. Failures are architecture-specific: auger motor running
        high amperage under load (precursor to stall and shutdown), gearbox bearing failure (audible grinding
        or whine), extrusion-chamber wear (nugget texture changes), and water-regulator issues affecting slush
        consistency. We've run enough Meridian calls across LA Chick-fil-A franchise groups to know the patterns
        cold.
      </p>
      <p>
        The fast-casual chain context matters operationally. Franchise operators running multiple LA locations
        usually want bulk-maintenance visits — one technician covering 3–5 locations across a region on a
        scheduled quarterly cycle — rather than emergency-only response. We quote that flexibly; the per-location
        economics work out better for everyone.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section alt">
    <div class="wrap narrow">
      <h2>Aquasphere sphere ice — premium cocktail bar luxury angle</h2>
      <p>
        Scotsman Aquasphere produces 1.5-inch spherical ice — a pre-formed ball that presents photographically
        in a rocks glass and melts noticeably slower than any cube format. The buyer pool in LA is narrow but
        specific: Michelin-level restaurant bar programs (Providence, Melisse, Saison-adjacent kitchens),
        five-star hotel cocktail bars (The Beverly Hills Hotel Polo Lounge, Hotel Bel-Air Bar, The Peninsula
        Beverly Hills), and the top tier of craft-cocktail speakeasies in WeHo and DTLA.
      </p>
      <p>
        From a service standpoint, Aquasphere is low-install-count work. That changes the service economics —
        fewer units in the parts network means specific-part lead times can run longer than standard Prodigy
        Plus components, and diagnostic tooling for the sphere-specific evaporator is less universally available.
        But when an Aquasphere unit fails in an LA luxury venue, the bar program's entire premium ice offering
        is at risk, so the call is always urgent. We prioritize response.
      </p>
      <p>
        Cross-reference for LA craft-cocktail operators: see our
        <a href="/brands/kold-draft-ice-machine-repair/">Kold-Draft ice machine repair page</a> for the 1-1/4-inch
